duces sec\ntionalism into public administration.\nGovernor\nCox is the would-be heir to an admisitration that\nstrives to solve every political problem by the\nortablishment of some bureau with power to tell\nthe American people from day to day in what\nmanner they shall conduct their affairs.\n\"Senator Harding is the spokesman i\nof\nthe\nparty that has always stood for America first, in\ntariff legislation, in development ot a merchant\nmarine, and in the negotiation and enforcement.\nof international treaties.\nsent* the party that repealed\nGovernor Cox repro-1\nthe\nprotective\ntariff. that repealed the provision for free tolls\nthe\nfor American coastwise shipping through\nI\nPanama Canal and that advised Americans to.\nget out of Mexico and forfeit their rights under\nHe is the spokesman ot j\ninternational treaties.\nthat party which would make America subject to\na super-state dominated hy Europe in general\nand by Great Britain in particular. Governor!\nCox is leader bf the party that proposes scuttle\nand surrender.\n\u201cSenator Harding is leader of\nthat\nparty\nwhich forced the curtailment of Federal appro-'\npriations to the extent of two and a bal-,bll\nlions.\nGovernor Cox is the defender of\nthe\nparty and administration that squandered money\nduring the war and sought to continue squander-,\ning after the war was over.\nSenator Harding is\nthe exponent of the obviously true doctrine that\nrational taxes can be reduced only by reduction\nof expenditures.\nGovernor Cox triese to delude1\nthe people by advocating reduction ot taxes at;\nthe same time that he defends the administra\ntion that tried to keep up expenditures.\n\"Senator Harding's party is for American na\ntionalism with peace: Governor Cox's party is\nfor an internationalism\nthat\nwould\ninvolve\nAmerica in every European or Asiatic broll.\n\"The choice between the men and the policies\nshould not be difficult.\" I\nWHY LANE QUIT HIH JOI!\nRegardless of the outcome of the\n1\nelection I\nI\nFranklin K. Lane, former Secretary of the In-\nterior, sees a bright business outlook, according)\nto a statement which he buses upon reporth from\nall parts of the country to the Fidelity and De-,\nposit Company of Baltimore.\nThe high coat of\nliving is the big Issue he sayw and adds that hoth|\n01 the campaigners seem to have overlooked it.!\nThe men directing the political campaigns mayj\nhave overlooked it says the National\nWei fu re l\nUnion of Washington but Mr. and\nMrs.\nCon-!\nnumer have their minda all made up about it Mr.\nLane will admit and while the political pell\npell\nbinders speak early and later the\nvoters\nill I\napeak only once but with some-effect on Novem\nher the second between certain hours as desig-\nrated hy law.\nMr. Lane. it may be\nrecalled.\nquit the cabinet some time ago to step out and\nI\nmake a living for his family before it was too\nlate, or in other words, for the reasons he fays!\nis now the big issue.\nThere are several others\nin the same fix but they do not dare quit the job\nthey have. Not being able to change jobs as Mr.\nLane did they will change government manage\nwent.\nWHY NOT ANBWERY\n\"It is a great and solemn referendum.\"\nThe\npeople have a right to know why Governor Cox'\nsaid he didn't. WHEN HE DID. accept campaign}\ncontribution from the Ohio Liquor League: why\nhe said he didn't WHEN HE DD, call out the\ntroops in an industrial dispute: why he says he\nis a progressive when in 1914 he\ndemanded\nTWICE OVER that the term PROGRESSIVE/\nSHOULD NOT BE APPLIED TO HIM?\nthe big Issues is sincerety and veracity.\nOne of!\nWhy\ndoes he charge a \"senatorial oligarchy,\" when!\nin the final analysis, his main support right now)\nis derived from Murphy. Taggert. Nugent, and\nBrennan? I\nGovernor Cox makes no progress in denounc\ning these questions,\nthem?\nWhy doesn't he answer\nI\nI\nMuch trouble could be averted If we could only\nunderstand what the other fellow is trying to\nbut that doesn't mean that understanding\nwould imply co-operation.\ndo:\nI\nI\nOne reason why the movies do not picture\nbeautiful scenes of domestic life is that\nthe\nbeautiful girls won't stay there long enough to\nhave t\n1*\n7\npictures taken. J\nXUSkRIIEs\nA MANB JOB.\nIt's a man\u2019s job to be cheerful\nin the face of grief and care;\nAny weakling can be tearful\nAnd a victim of despair.\nBut It takes a man to swallow\nAll the bitter in the cup.\nAnd to live for what may follow.\nWithout ever giving up.\nI\nIt's a man\u2019s job to be kindly,\nit's a man's job to be true;\nNone can shut his eyes and blindly\nTry to journey this life through\nAnd not see the wrongs about him\n0\nOr the hazards in his way;\nThere are times when fate will flout him\nAnd his feet will go astray.\nI\nNot In fools and craven creatures\nAre the worthy virtues found.\nNot on blank and lifeless features\nDo the cheerful smiles abound;\nHe who to his best is living\nAnd for truth and honor stands.\nAnd is cheerful in his giving.\nHas a man's job on his hands.\nTo be kind and thoughtful ever.\nTo be strong in times of need,\nTo put all your hest endeavor\nIn an effort to succeed.\nAnd to fall and keep on trying.\nAnd not lose your cheerful ways,\nis a joh, there's no denying.\nFor a real man, nowadays.\n\nPARAGRAPHIC PONTH.\nIn estimating the value of a ball player here\nafter. must we have his baiting.\nfielding and\nbribing averages?\u2014Detroit Free Press.\nWe pay double for restaurant pie.\nFirst in\ncash and secondly in discomfort.\u2014Toledo Blade.\nThe Prohibitien party candidate for president\nhas an easy job.\nHe can say anything he pleases\nwithout endangering the chances of his election\n\u2014Pittsburg Gazette-Times.\nWe wonder what excuse those 10,000,000 peo\nple give for living in New York when they\ncan\nlive in Ohio and have the chance to be a presi\ndent.\u2014Cincinnati Enquirer.\nBook publishers indicate that the output of Ac\ntion is Increasing.\nmuch, if they would be frank.\u2014\nColonel F. W Galbraith has\nPoliticians might indicato as\nChicago News.\nbeen elected\nCommander of the American Legion. From waat\nstate does he hail?\nHow can you ask?\nFrom\nOhio, of course.\u2014 Chicago News.\nIf the worst comes to the worst we might go\nback to croquet as the national game.\nNo bet\nting scandal has touched that great pastime.\u2014\nCincinnati Enquirer.\nA Chicago apartment-house owner has announ\nced a reduction of rents.\nThis sort of announce\nment ought not to be allow\n2\nror\nIt causes many\ntenants who are not ovely strong to die of shock.\nHouston Post.\nWe suggest a straw vote to determine whether\n115,000,000 would be too much to pay for a\nchange.\u2014Toledo Blade.\nKey West shows a decrease in population, by\nthe census, but it has a perfect alibi.\nIt is diffi\ncult keeping people st home to be counted in a\ntown that is near Cuba.- Cleveland Press.\nWe often wonder to whom the\nGovernment\nsnda those warnings against counterfeit hun\ndred dollar bills.\nWe never have received one.\n\u2014Cincinnati Enquirer.\nTHINK THIH OVER.\n1\n\u201cIt is a time for clear thinking and straight\ntalking.\"\nThe quotation is from the remarks of\nCov\nl\nWell. then\u2014this is far from admit\nting the fact, but even if the Wilson League of\nerner Cox,\nNations were the best thing in the world. which)\nIt isn\u2019t. on the record James M. Cox has made\nin this campaign for statemanilke,calm and bal\na nee. vision. grasp of vital problems, dignity, re\nstraint, sincerity. veracity, prudence.\npatience..\nurbanity, wisdom. knowledge, foresight, moral\ncourage. patriotism. etc., can the people of the'\nUnited States seriously consider him\nfor\nthe\nh'gh office of president of the United States?\nI\nRipplingRhumes\n46 5 Walt Mason,,\u201dAA\nI\n2 I\nI\n1119 S--\u2014\nTHE zO:\nI sometimes go to see the Zoo, where shelf\nworn Bruin rages, and moldy lions, grim\nand\nI sue, look forth from rusty cages.\nAnd there are\nI\nwolves from forests dark, and monkeys tenor\nseven; and weary critters howl and bark and\n>end their walls to heaven. All day they paco;\nthe sodden floor (save when the keepers feed\n'em land stick their noses through the door, and\nyearn and yelp for freedom.\nThey're dreaming\nof the jungles deep where once they gayly gam\nholed. or of the mountains wild and steep where\nin their youth they scrambled. They're thinking\nof the forest dense, of wood lore strange and\nclever; and now behind an Iron fence they're\ndoomed to pace forever.\nNo more for these un\nhappy beasts the hunting call and rally; no more\nfor them the outlaw feasts in desert, swamp or\nvalley.\nNo more in some vast silent land will\ntheir swift feet be racing; and idle human beings\nstand, and watch their tireless pacing.\nWe\u2019ve\nput these sad-eyed brutes in jail. without a writ\nor warrant. In musty cages foul and stale. with\natmosphere abhorrent.\nThey did not booze or\nbeat their wives, or do some speed law sinning;\nthey merely tried bo live their lives as planned\nlu the beginning.\nAnd now the poor moth-eaten\nwrecks behind the bars must languish, that idle,\nsnooping rubbernecks may view their, endless\nanguish. e:\nREXALL VOTE\nI\nON PRESIDENT\nThe result of the Rexall\nvote on the president, local.\nstraw\nstate\nand national today is as followe: I\nLocal\nI\nMen\nWomen\nTotal\nHarding\n500\n207\n707\nCox\n301\n127:\n428\nMen\nWomen\nTotal\nMen\nWomen\nHtate\nHarding\n23.008\n_ 8.824\n31.832\nNational\nHarding\n249.1 44\n85,506\nI\nCox\n11.688\n8.795\n15,483\n1\nCox\n165.433 I\n48.944 i\nTotal 334.650 214,377\nThe electoral college according to\nthe straw vote stands 353 votes for\nHarding, 178 for Cox. a -total of 531.\nnecessary to choice. 266. I\nI\nSchuler\u2019s! Schuler\u2019s dancing I\nsnools opens at new armory 1\nMonday eve, Oct. 11. New be- j\nginners class 7:30. Assemblv 9-\n11:30, Hipp. orch. Mr. and Mrs.\nSchuler will demonstrate fox\ntrot combinations and Winton\nwaltz.\nsept 39 oct 1-2-5-6-7-8-9\nFo